> The best suggestion I've heard so far is that the valve guide maybe tight and after breakin the valve will seat properly. Opinions?

If it's just tight you should be able to tap the valve home and see if
it seals with a poor man's leak down test, filling the combustion
chamber with gasoline and see if it leaks into the ports.

